trans-unit.source: <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> supports the SERIALIZABLE (RR), REPEATABLE (RS), READ COMMITTED (CS), and READ UNCOMMITTED (UR) isolation levels.

seg-source.mrk: <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> supports the SERIALIZABLE (RR), REPEATABLE (RS), READ COMMITTED (CS), and READ UNCOMMITTED (UR) isolation levels.

target.mrk: <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> supports the SERIALIZABLE (RR), REPEATABLE (RS), READ COMMITTED (CS), and READ UNCOMMITTED (UR) isolation levels.

trans-unit.source: CS (the default isolation level) provides the best balance between concurrency and consistency in multiple-client environments.

seg-source.mrk: CS (the default isolation level) provides the best balance between concurrency and consistency in multiple-client environments.

target.mrk: CS (the default isolation level) provides the best balance between concurrency and consistency in multiple-client environments.

trans-unit.source: RS provides less consistency than RR but allows more concurrency.

seg-source.mrk: RS provides less consistency than RR but allows more concurrency.

target.mrk: RS provides less consistency than RR but allows more concurrency.

trans-unit.source: UR provides maximum concurrency, if uncommitted values are allowed in the query. It is typically used if approximate results are acceptable.
